description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you patient focused and want to have a role in better outcomes for patients? Want to be part of a dynamic, supportive and multi-disciplinary team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering permanent roles, but we are open to consider 12 month secondments from local NHS health systems in Derbyshire, Nottinghamshire or Leicestershire&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come and join us as we shape our new wave of expansion and transformation within our Integrated Discharge Team at Nottingham University Hospital NHS Trust. This is a truly exciting opportunity to work with a great team, build on our success and help us develop to achieve more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for passionate individuals who enjoy working with a range of diverse teams, as we work across our hospital and our community partners. You need to be patient centred and able to work with compassion with our patients and their families as they make their transition out of hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This critical role will help those patients with more complex needs, where they need a ‘supported’ discharge to leave hospital in a safe and timely way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for the next step and a rewarding career, then come and join the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Cameron - Team Manager - 0115 9249924 Ext 89486&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Harrison Team Manager - helen.harrison@nuh.nhs.uk 0115 9249924 Ext 89486&lt;/p&gt;
